         <abstract label="abstract">In 1949, New Jersey newspaper editor Robert N. Caldwell began a
            close friendship with his former professor at Columbia University, Mark van Doren. The
            two frequently discussed politics, literature, philosophy, and their day-to-day lives.
            This collection consists of correspondence, between Robert Caldwell and Columbia
            professor Mark van Doren spanning two decades.</abstract>
